 with the Homestake, GALLEX, and SAGE experiments. This happens\nbecause the former detects not only the solar \\nu_e but also, at a lower cross\nsection, the oscillated solar \\bar\\nu_e; while the latter are sensitive only to\nthe oscillation-diminished solar \\nu_e flux. A direct observation of solar\n\\bar\\nu_e by SNO will confirm our scenario. Finally, we consider the\npossibility for flavor-dependent gravitational couplings of neutrinos as\nemerging out of the noncommutativity of the quantum operators associated with\nthe measurements of energy and flavor.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Jul 1998 03:10:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Aug 1998 17:06:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-06"}
